                        {
                            "type": "heading",
                            "text": "Creating a Composition from Footage"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "After Effects is all about creating compositions - combining, or compositing, different audio and visual elements like text, video, and sounds, and then making them move in fun and creative ways."
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "The first step of any After Effects project is to import the media you’ll be working with and create a composition."
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "listSubsteps",
                            "listItems": [
                                {
                                    "text": "In the <$Composition panel$>, click on <$New Composition From Footage$>."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "First select the Adobe Illustrator file APEAK_Logo.ai. Then change the <$Import as$> setting from “Footage” to “<$Composition$>” and click <${BUTTON.IMPORT_IN_DIALOG.{{osName}}}$>.",
                                    "checkUserInteractions": [
                                        {
                                            "check": "projectItemAdded",
                                            "payload": {
                                                "itemType": "composition"
                                            }
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "showOnComplete": {
                                        "heading": "Success!",
                                        "texts": [
                                            "Look over in the {{definition:{TOOLTIP.PROJECT_PANEL}|Project panel}}. You should now see two items: the composition you just created from the logo and a folder with the original logo files."
                                        ]
                                    }
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "stepActionsOnShow": [
                        {
                            "actionName": "setItemSelected",
                            "payload": {
                                "itemName": "APEAK_Logo",
                                "selected": false
                            }
                        }
                    ],
                    "stepItems": [
                        {
                            "type": "video",
                            "videoUrl": "{{pathPanelPayloadsWithKey}}opening-comp.mp4",
                            "autoplay": true,
                            "loop": true
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "heading",
                            "text": "Opening the Composition"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "Now that you’ve created the {{definition:{TOOLTIP.COMPOSITION}|composition}}, you will need to open it in the <$Timeline panel$> so that you can edit it."
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "listSubsteps",
                            "listItems": [
                                {
                                    "text": "Double-click on the <$APEAK_Logo$> composition in the Project panel.",
                                    "checkUserInteractions": [
                                        {
                                            "check": "isCompositionActive",
                                            "payload": {
                                                "compositionName": "APEAK_Logo"
                                            }
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "showOnComplete": {
                                        "heading": "Success!",
                                        "texts": [
                                            "Look over in the {{definition:{TOOLTIP.COMPOSITION_PANEL}|Composition panel}}. The logo is now displayed on screen. Now look at the {{definition:{TOOLTIP.TIMELINE_PANEL}|Timeline panel}}. The files <$APEAK$> (the logo text) and <$Logo$> (the logo itself) were added to the Timeline panel and correspond to what you see in the Composition panel."
                                        ]
                                    }
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "stepItems": [
                        {
                            "type": "endScreen",
                            "successHeading": "Great Job!",
                            "successText": "You just learned how to create a composition using existing media files. Next, you’ll learn how to organize your composition."
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
